@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@
+# Solution
+
+`get` returned live entries without moving them to the most-recently-used end of the `OrderedDict`, so a later insertion could evict an entry that had just been read. It now refreshes recency after confirming the entry has not expired.
+
+`put` evicted the least-recently-used entry whenever the cache was full, even when the key being written already existed. Eviction is now performed only for a new key, allowing existing entries to be updated in place and marked most recently used.
